<br>
That being said, I do not have manaburn yet, since I have not been playing much for about 4 months. I can nonetheless comment on what wizard PvP was _before_ manaburn.<br>
<br>
The casting of _any_ regular DD is too random to be of any use. You won't do a dent to anyone with good resists. The only spell that you can cast reliably in PvP are lures. Now the problem with lures is that they are 4.5 second casting. This can be brought down to 4.0 if you have a level 3 CLASS AA ability.<br>
<br>
With a 4.5 casting spell, from the moment a melee with jboots (or even now with run 3) enters casting range and the moment the melee is on me, there is a little over 2 seconds. This is not eevn time to get of a 3.0 normal DD, much less a 4.5 lure without being hit.<br>
<br>
My testing shows that the channeling of a 4.5 second level 60 lure (our only good damage lure) is of about 25% (figure taken against a monk with a T-Staff) after about 2 seconds melle against him.<br>
<br>
That means to do 825 x 0.66 = 519 damage to a melee I need to be on average hit in melee for an equivalent of 4x 2 seconds lets say about 4x 200 damage (I'm being really nice here)<br>
<br>
Also remember that after this I have a melee on my tail, and I need to run from him, and be able to cast yonder _and_ get a good distance yonder, all this without getting hit.<br>
<br>
Does this sound fair for a wiz vs. melee? Does this sound balanced?<br>
<br>
Wiz are very good vs. other int based casters because they do less DPS to us and much less reliably, pets aren't all a problem, except for epic mage pets who do _huge_ damage, with a proc over 200 damage that's hard to resist, but still they can be dealt with.<br>
<br>
The problem in PvP lies with the fact that in general int casters &lt; melee. And that the int casters best pvp weapon is gate. Maybe for Mr. Rogue the best defense is offense, but for the most offensive INT caster class, the best defense, and might I add the best PvP tactic once you are faced with a melee in single combat is gate. Now, I might add that gate is overpowered, because being able to have a clean getaway is a very important advantage, but is there a possibility that this same wizard is going to take down that melee? No.<br>
<br>
Wiz &gt; int casters in PvP<br>
Wiz &lt; melee in PvP<br>
<br>
And as a matter of fact with manaburn it's pretty much the same thing. Wizards are single shotting OTHER int casters, not melees, because other casters can't run up to melee range and interrupt you.<br>
<br>
That's in my eyes the greateest problem with MB, it favors wiz vs. other casters, where wiz were balanced, but does not change much to wiz vs. melee. <p>Aurore
